			<h3 >
								<a href="#p47981">Re: Secure file deletion</a>
			</h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=47981&amp;sid=8cf1235613d6d69890daf1635e23f414#p47981"><img src="./styles/Carbon/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>			by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14322&amp;sid=8cf1235613d6d69890daf1635e23f414">Goatboy</a></strong> on Sat Oct 23, 2010 11:50 pm			<br />([msg=47981]see Re: Secure file deletion[/msg])
			</p>

			
			<div class="content">I'm not sure what you mean by digitally shredding.  Did you think that they &quot;shread&quot; the file into little places and put them all over the drive?  That would simply be ridiculous.  Digital shredding means erasing the file, as you mentioned in your first option.</div>

